## ğŸ§  Overview
This project is a Python-based tool designed to extract text and images from educational PDF files. It organizes the extracted data into a structured JSON format, making it suitable for applications such as automated question generation, e-learning tools, and content indexing.

---

## ğŸ“‚ Features
- âœ… Extracts text from each page of a PDF.
- ğŸ–¼ï¸ Extracts and saves all embedded images per page.
- ğŸ“„ Generates a structured `output.json` with:
  - Page number
  - Question text (first line of page text or placeholder)
  - Main image
  - Option images
- ğŸ’¾ Saves all images with page and image number.

